Class LogEntryReader

    • Method Detail

      • readLogEntries

        public static List<LogEntry> readLogEntries(java.lang.String file)
                                     throws java.io.FileNotFoundException
        Reads each user activity log from the input file and adds each log to the list of log entries. Returns an unsorted list of log entries. This method will be used under the assumption that the file provided is correctly formated.
        Parameters:
        file - the input file containing log entry information to read
        Returns:
        the unsorted list of log entries
        Throws:
        java.io.FileNotFoundException - if a problem occurred when processing the file

      • writeLogEntries

        public static void writeLogEntries(java.lang.String fileName,
                                   ArrayBasedList<LogEntry> entries)
                            throws java.io.IOException
        Writes the given list of log entries to a file. If there is a problem with writing to the file, then an IOException is thrown. Note that the method was referenced from the CourseRecordsIO class from the PackScheduler project from CSC216 lab.
        Parameters:
        fileName - the file to write the log entries in
        entries - the list of log entries
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if there is a problem writing to the file
